data.name: ExternalConstraintConnectAction.SetComparisonConstraint.Instructions
data.value:
To select role sequences to populate the constraint: -Click a role or subtype line to add it to the active role sequence -Control-Click a role or subtype line to remove it from the active role sequence -Double-Click a role to commit the active role sequence and begin a new role sequence -Click the diagram background or press Escape to cancel an uncommitted role sequence
If a subtype is constrained use single-click to add and double-click to commit.
data.comment: The text shown to explain how to hook up an external constraint to its associated roles.

data.name: ExternalConstraintConnectAction.SetConstraint.Instructions
data.value: To select role sequences to populate the constraint: -Click a role or subtype line to add it to the constraint -Control-Click a role or subtype line to remove it from the constaint -Double-Click a role or subtype line to commit -Click the diagram background or press Escape to cancel
data.comment: The text shown to explain how to hook up an external constraint to its associated roles.

data.comment: The format string for a role player with a () qualifier in the FactEditor. The qualifier represents either a value type or a reference mode. Languages which should not rely on capitalization to delimit ObjectType names should put square braces around this format string.

data.name: MessageBox.CopyMergeExtensionRequired.Message
data.value:
The completed copy/merge operation ignored elements from extensions not enabled in this model.
Would you like to enable the following extensions?
— {0}
Yes: Undo the operation and load the extensions. You will need to manually repeat the merge operation after the document reloads. No: Do not load the extensions and do not ask again for these extensions in this document in this session of NORMA. Cancel: Keep the current state and continue to ask this question.
data.comment: The message displayed if a merge operation is attempted but not all extensions are enabled.

data.name: MessageBox.CopyMergeExtensionRequired.Message.JoinSeparator
data.comment: The join separator to combine multiple missing extension names in the MessageBox.CopyMergeExtensionRequired.Message.

data.comment: The message displayed if a selected item cannot be located in the model browser.

data.name: MessageBox.ExtensionLoadFailure.Message
data.value: One or more registered extensions could not be resolved and will be unavailable.{0}
data.comment: The message displayed if initial extension verification fails to resolve and verify the type for an extension.

data.name: MessageBox.ExtensionLoadFailure.Message.Line
data.comment: Format each line. These are concatenated and attached to the end of the MessageBox.ExtensionLoadFailure.Message. Replacements: {0}=extension namespace,{1}=error message

data.name: MessageBox.RevertExtensions.Message
data.value: Restoring previous model state, loading new extensions failed with exception:
data.comment: The header for the message displayed if a set of extensions fails to correctly reload.

data.name: MessageBox.ImpliedInternalUniquenessConstraint.Message
data.value: One or more of the internal uniqueness constraints are implied by other internal uniqueness constraints. Would you like to remove the implied constraints?
data.comment: The message for the auto-fix implied internal uniqueness constraint message box.

data.name: MessageBox.FileFormatUpgrade.Message
data.value: The file format of '{0}' has been automatically upgraded to a new version. Should the 'Save' command be disabled to preserve the original file contents? The 'Save As' command will remain enabled.
data.comment: The message shown when a file is upgraded to a new format. Replacement field 0 is the file name.

data.name: MessageBox.FinalShapeDeletion.Message
data.value: The final shape corresponding to this element is being deleted. Delete the underlying '{0}' element '{1}' as well?
data.comment: The message for the prompt to delete an element from the model when the final shape representing it is delete. Replacement field 0 gets the class name and 1 the component name.

data.name: MessageBox.UnrecognizedExtensionsStripped.Message
data.value: The file format of '{0}' contains unsupported extensions. Data associated with extension(s) '{1}' has been removed. Should the 'Save' command be disabled to preserve the original file contents? The 'Save As' command will remain enabled.
data.comment: The message shown when extensions are automatically removed from a file. Replacements: {0}=file name, {1}=list of unrecognized extensions.
